Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.58,0:03:15.79,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Even the world's billions of heartbeats
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.79,0:03:22.72,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Are nothing to you but a fleeting and insignificant question
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.72,0:03:27.76,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}We may be trapped in the past or lament the future
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.76,0:03:33.69,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}But predetermination does not allow the slightest mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.69,0:03:39.94,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}The infinite dreams and imagined futures before us
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.94,0:03:45.74,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Are naught but vain theories we may hold
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.74,0:03:51.79,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(0,250)}Finitude is what the two clock hands show
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.79,0:03:56.54,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(250,0)}As they point toward a cruel destiny and choice
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.46,0:04:05.68,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3\fad(1000,0}And now I cross the boundary between worlds each second
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.68,0:04:10.72,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Because I want to protect that smile of yours
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.72,0:04:17.65,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}And a loop in time without sadness will once again
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.65,0:04:23.90,OP Eng,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}Engulf me, a lonely observer
